**1. How high would you have to count before you would use the letter "A" in the English language spelling of a whole number?**
You would have to count all the way to **one thousand** (1,000).

If you spell out the numbers from zero to nine hundred ninety-nine, you will not find the letter "A". It does not appear in "one," "two," "three," "hundred," or any combination thereof. The first time the letter appears is in the word "thousand."

